<font color="#FF0000">COMMENT ON SADNESS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15  1:24:40 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I wondered what my Brother would think and feel if he were alive to view your comments. He was a Vet who suffered a slow death long after he left the war. Vietnam was an orgy of power and an exercise in sheer greed. Our values were shattered by suicidal children and commodity trading in human skin. I suspect and hope that we never do this again. Yet, I look to the Indians in the rainforests and see the same activities. The real culprits were and are Dupont, Dow Chemical, Big Oil and all the wannabees. Their legacy is a polluted country and damaged children. The only one with any guts, Zumwalt, lived through the early death of his Son and the genetic ruin of his Grandson. Bless you all for going and not going. There was no way to win this one. 
<p><code>-- duane_hoffman@bc.sympatico.ca/  (Duane Hoffman) </code><p>


